One of my favorite places to go when I need my Caribbean cuisine fix. The Jerk Chicken is second to none. It has that perfect balance between mild and spicy and is full of flavor. A lot of the caribbean places that I've  been don't execute flavor well. Prices are about average for Caribbean spots. A large platter can range from 9.50 to about 20.00 depending on your choice of meat (chicken, fish, goat, ox). Well worth a visit if you're in the Mt. Vernon or West Baltimore area.

This place is a whole in the wall. Make no mistake about that. However after discovering the authentic Caribbean Taste that this place has to offer have to give four stars. The jerk chicken is not what the Caribbean people would call oven jerk. It's actually made on a grill which is authentic exclamation point the curry goat was tender well-seasoned and unfortunately was so good I couldn't keep the other Forks out of my plate if you know what I mean. In Jamaica macaroni and cheese is called macaroni pie , however the macaroni pie here was not up to par. Also they need to add Sorrel to the menu. Bottom line the majority of their food is authentic tasting well-seasoned and makes this place worth the visit exclamation point
